findings.title: Potential unauthorized script upgrade
findings.description: The smart contract may allow an unauthorized user to upgrade the script, potentially leading to malicious behavior.

findings.title: Non-whitelisted wallet can only transfer a specified number of tokens
findings.description: A non-whitelisted wallet has a limitation on the number of tokens it can transfer.

findings.title: Non-whitelisted wallet can only hold a specified number of tokens
findings.description: A non-whitelisted wallet has a limitation on the number of tokens it can hold.

findings.title: Smart Contract Owner Authorization Persistence
findings.description: The smart contract owner can authorize a wallet to modify 'write contract' parameters, and when ownership is transferred, the previous owner remains authorized.
